columns_to_plot = [col for col in df.columns if col not in ['name', 'status']]
In [12]:
# Create a bar plot for each column
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
for col in columns_to_plot:
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(data=df, x='status', y=col)
    plt.title(f'Bar plot of {col} by Status')
    plt.xlabel('Status')
    plt.ylabel(col)
    plt.show()
In [13]:
num_cols = 3
num_plots = len(columns_to_plot)
num_rows = (num_plots + num_cols - 1) // num_cols
sns.set(style="whitegrid")
fig, axes = plt.subplots(num_rows, num_cols, figsize=(18, num_rows * 5))


axes = axes.flatten()
for idx in range(len(columns_to_plot)):
    col = columns_to_plot[idx]
    sns.barplot(data=df, x='status', y=col, ax=axes[idx])
    axes[idx].set_title(f'Bar plot of {col} by Status')
    axes[idx].set_xlabel('Status')
    axes[idx].set_ylabel(col)
    
for i in range(num_plots, len(axes)):
    fig.delaxes(axes[i])
    
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
